f Jamal Siddiqui","target":"Author/Arif Jamal Siddiqui","line":96},{"title":"Author/Mitesh Patel","target":"Author/Mitesh Patel","line":97},{"title":"Author/Mitesh Patel","target":"Author/Mitesh Patel","line":98},{"title":"Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem","target":"Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem","line":99},{"title":"Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem","target":"Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem","line":100},{"title":"Author/Mejdi Snoussi","target":"Author/Mejdi Snoussi","line":101},{"title":"Author/Mejdi Snoussi","target":"Author/Mejdi Snoussi","line":102},{"title":"Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf","target":"Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf","line":103},{"title":"Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf","target":"Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf","line":104},{"title":"Author/Mohd Adnan","target":"Author/Mohd Adnan","line":105},{"title":"Author/Mohd Adnan","target":"Author/Mohd Adnan","line":106},{"title":"Author/Sibte Hadi","target":"Author/Sibte Hadi","line":107},{"title":"Author/Sibte Hadi","target":"Author/Sibte Hadi","line":108},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/ashraf_cordycepin_2020/ashraf_cordycepin_2020.pdf","line":110}],"metadata":{"id":"ashraf_cordycepin_2020","type":"article-journal","title":"Cordycepin for Health and Wellbeing: A Potent Bioactive Metabolite of an Entomopathogenic Medicinal Fungus Cordyceps with Its Nutraceutical and Therapeutic Potential","issued":{"date-parts":[[2020]]},"DOI":"10.3390/molecules25122735","container-title":"Molecules","abstract":"Cordyceps is a rare naturally occurring entomopathogenic fungus usually found at high altitudes on the Himalayan plateau and a well-known medicinal mushroom in traditional Chinese medicine. Cordyceps contains various bioactive components, out of which, cordycepin is considered most vital, due to its utmost therapeutic as well as nutraceutical potential. Moreover, the structure similarity of cordycepin with adenosine makes it an important bioactive component, with difference of only hydroxyl group, lacking in the 3′ position of its ribose moiety. Cordycepin is known for various nutraceutical and therapeutic potential, such as anti-diabetic, anti-hyperlipidemia, anti-fungal, anti-inflammatory, immunomodulatory, antioxidant, anti-aging, anticancer, antiviral, hepato-protective, hypo-sexuality, cardiovascular diseases, antimalarial, anti-osteoporotic, anti-arthritic, cosmeceutical etc. which makes it a most valuable medicinal mushroom for helping in maintaining good health. In this review, effort has been made to bring altogether the possible wide range of cordycepin’s nutraceutical potential along with its pharmacological actions and possible mechanism. Additionally, it also summarizes the details of cordycepin based nutraceuticals predominantly available in the market with expected global value. Moreover, this review will attract the attention of food scientists, nutritionists, pharmaceutical and food industries to improve the use of bioactive molecule cordycepin for nutraceutical purposes with commercialization to aid and promote healthy lifestyle, wellness and wellbeing.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Ashraf","given":"Syed Amir","literal":""},{"family":"Ashraf","given":"Syed Amir","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Elkhalifa","given":"Abd Elmoneim O.","literal":""},{"family":"Siddiqui","given":"Arif Jamal","literal":""},{"family":"Siddiqui","given":"Arif Jamal","literal":""},{"family":"Patel","given":"Mitesh","literal":""},{"family":"Patel","given":"Mitesh","literal":""},{"family":"Awadelkareem","given":"Amir Mahgoub","literal":""},{"family":"Awadelkareem","given":"Amir Mahgoub","literal":""},{"family":"Snoussi","given":"Mejdi","literal":""},{"family":"Snoussi","given":"Mejdi","literal":""},{"family":"Ashraf","given":"Mohammad Saquib","literal":""},{"family":"Ashraf","given":"Mohammad Saquib","literal":""},{"family":"Adnan","given":"Mohd","literal":""},{"family":"Adnan","given":"Mohd","literal":""},{"family":"Hadi","given":"Sibte","literal":""},{"family":"Hadi","given":"Sibte","literal":""}],"citation-key":"ashraf_cordycepin_2020","year":"2020","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Cordycepin for Health and Wellbeing: A Potent Bioactive Metabolite of an Entomopathogenic Medicinal Fungus Cordyceps with Its Nutraceutical and Therapeutic Potential"],"author-links":["[[Author/Syed Amir Ashraf]]","[[Author/Syed Amir Ashraf]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Abd Elmoneim O. Elkhalifa]]","[[Author/Arif Jamal Siddiqui]]","[[Author/Arif Jamal Siddiqui]]","[[Author/Mitesh Patel]]","[[Author/Mitesh Patel]]","[[Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem]]","[[Author/Amir Mahgoub Awadelkareem]]","[[Author/Mejdi Snoussi]]","[[Author/Mejdi Snoussi]]","[[Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf]]","[[Author/Mohammad Saquib Ashraf]]","[[Author/Mohd Adnan]]","[[Author/Mohd Adnan]]","[[Author/Sibte Hadi]]","[[Author/Sibte Hadi]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/ashraf_cordycepin_2020/ashraf_cordycepin_2020.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"3gjg16","at":1774951886749}},"smart_blocks:Research/@ashraf_cordycepin_2020.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.06597587,-0.03074981,0.01580759,-0.01316857,0.03447147,-0.00571604,0.04214602,0.08828752,-0.04019272,-0.00454147,0.00963751,-0.07862066,0.00088838,-0.02362139,0.01198692,0.00623618,0.0199997,0.05518902,-0.12224076,0.03760461,0.09122613,0.00113328,-0.02575547,-0.01274158,0.01791226,0.05533952,-0.02713694,-0.0136155,-